You can have the canon for the price of a regular sandwich roaster (2000$).

This morning when I cleaned my bathroom, I accidently mixed Cleanup BANG!© with TNT Toilet Fresher©. The next thing I remember was a giant blast and realizing that my bathroom was gone.
Penny, my cat, has been missing ever since. If you find my litte darling, I'll give you the rest of my cleaning stuff.
Will you find Penny? (2000$).

PLAY
Create falling rocks
Creating a falling rock is done in two steps:
1. Click in the area to choose a horisontal start position of the rock.
2. Click againg to choose the rock's start direction and create it.
An indicator arrow will appear when hovering the area, and will assist in chosing both position and direction of the rock.
Choose a rock type
Click on a rock icon to choose the type of rocks that you want to create.
Save your level
Click to save your level. You will have to play through the level before it is saved. This is done to ensure that the level can be completed, and to calculate the levels difficulty.
When saved your level will appear in the game!
YOU WILL NOT BE ABLE TO CHANGE THE LEVEL AFTERWARDS
Try your level
Welcome to the level editor
Take a look at the tooltips to get a feeling of how the editor works.
When you feel ready to start creating your own levels, click the continue button below.

Instructions
For reasons unknown different sorts of gigantic rocks keep falling down on Cliff City.
To keep the city safe, a rocket firing cannon has been installed on the building in the middle.
Your objective is to use the cannon to shoot the falling rocks. Take aim with the cursor and click to fire a rocket in the mouse's direction.
This is where the rocks keep falling from
